<title>Traffic</title>

<section>
	<title>Introduction</title>
	<para>
		<libraryname>Traffic</libraryname> is a software system used for teaching introductory 
		programming. It consists of a library - the <projectname>Traffic library</projectname> -
		and <!--tobeincluded three--> two example applications that use the <projectname>Traffic library</projectname>: 
		<projectname>Flathunt</projectname><!--tobeincluded, <projectname>Touch</projectname>--> and <projectname>
		City3D</projectname>. The goal of <projectname>Traffic</projectname> is to make learning 
		to program exciting, interesting and realistic.
	</para>
</section>

